<item>
            <title>[DERBY-5314] Enable i18n tests in non-English locales</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-5314</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The i18n tests are disabled if they are running in non-English locales. It would be good to have them running regardless of the locale.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In Ole&apos;s nightly tests they are not running on Windows because of this. Seen for example last night when the i18n tests failed on all platforms, except on Windows:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://dbtg.foundry.sun.com/derby/test/Daily/jvm1.6/testing/Limited/testSummary-1143118.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://dbtg.foundry.sun.com/derby/test/Daily/jvm1.6/testing/Limited/testSummary-1143118.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There have been various improvements in ScriptTestCase lately to allow the canon-based tests to run in non-English locales, so I think it&apos;s safe to enable them now.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
